---
title: One-Pot Sausage and Tortelloni Soup with Baby Spinach in a Tomato Broth
description: Give the dishwasher a break tonight: all you need to put this recipe together is a pot and a couple utensils for stirring and chopping. But just because it involves minimal effort doesn’t mean that it has minimal flavor. Loaded with cheesy tortelloni, slices of sweet sausage, tender spinach leaves, and a tomato-y broth, the soup brims and bubbles with plenty of filling, Italian-inspired flavors.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w12-r6-414dc501.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w12-r6-8828aadf.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-sausage-and-tortelloni-soup-589a1510803b505daf7cd6d2
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 520 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 28 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1330 mg
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Thinly slice @sweet Italian pork sausage{9%oz} into rounds.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add sausage and cook until browned, ~{2-4%minutes} total. Remove from pot and set aside. Add onion, @garlic powder{2%tsp}, and @dried oregano{1%tsp} to pot. Cook, tossing, until just softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Return sausage to pot, along with @crushed tomatoes{2%14oz boxes}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @water{}(5 cups). Stir, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pot. Bring to a boil, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once soup is boiling, add @cheese tortelloni{9%oz}. Let cook until tender, about ~{8%minutes}.

Stir @spinach{5%oz} and @parsley{1/4%oz} into pot and let wilt. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{1/2%cup} and @chili flakes{1%tsp}(to taste).

> You might want to skip the chili flakes for the kids.